Miriam was found shot dead in her apartment.

Source: www.liminalis.org and O Tempo, 02.03.2009

D. was shot several times in the back and abdomen at dawn on Wednesday 4th March on East Avenue West in the central area of the city. She died at the scene.

> According to the Military Police, witnesses reported that they heard the noise of a motorcycle and then the sound of the shots. A man wearing a silver helment was then seen running away from a black motorbike.
> 
> This is the second case of murder of a trans woman in Londrina this year. The first took place on January 19, on Avenida 10 de Dezembro. The victim was struck by seven knife strokes.

D.'s death was not recorded on the official TDOR 2009 list released by Transgender Europe (TGEU).

Ebru was also known as Dilan Pirinc. She had received death threats before being stabbed to death in her apartment.

> Ebru had asked the Prosecutor's Office for protection from the man who had beaten her on several occasions and threatened to kill her. Lambda Istanbul was told that a few weeks ago police detained the man but released him two hours later. The same man is under police custody as the murder suspect."  -Press Release from Human Rights Watch,   March 13, 2009

Adriana was a sex worker. Her cause of death was not reported.

Sources: Portal Sida, 13.03.2009 & Anodis, 17.03.2009 and www.liminalis.de

Virgen was a sex worker. She was shot multiple times between 19th and 21st March.

Police suspect that she was murdered by a client when he realised that she was trans. Afterwards he threw her body into the river.

El Sol de Sinaloa 24.03.2009

Eda's body was found in a rubbish container in Bursa on 22 March 2009.

Her head and sexual organs had been cut off.

She was reportedly of Maghrebi and/or Moroccan origin.
